The paper deals with the problem of finding sparse solutions of underdetermined systems of linear equations, which is a fundamental problem in compressed sensing (cs). The paper proposes optimally tuned algorithms for this problem, which involves iterative reconstruction (IT) techniques. Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves extensive computation and optimization, which suggests that it may belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as well. The paper also discusses the robustness of the algorithms to different amplitude distributions and matrix ensembles, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper mentions the application of compressed sensing in image processing, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
